configset  GLOBAL  archive_url = [VALUE]
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
configset listname archive_url = [VALUE]
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
Default Value : 
Data Type     : string
Variable Group: archive
Password Notes: Visible only with password. 
= = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = =

EXAMPLE:
configset listname archive_url = http://www.mydomain.org/archives/


The URL at which public list archives are made accessible.

The URL can be used in variable substitution if the ARCURL variable
is added to message headers (see "help configset message_headers"),
to support RFC 2369. It is also used by the WWW interface (mj_wwwusr).


See Also:
   help variables (for a list of all possible variables and what they mean)
   help configset message_headers    (to put this string into post headers)

For a list of all help topics send this one-line message
   help topics
to the server at $MJ
